## Additional Historical Notes

### Serre's GAGA (Geometrie Algebrique et Geometrie Analytique)
In 1956, Serre established the comparison between algebraic and
analytic geometry for projective varieties over C. Key results:
- Coherent algebraic sheaves correspond to coherent analytic sheaves
- Cohomology groups agree: H^i_alg(X, F) = H^i_an(X^an, F^an)
- Chow's theorem: closed analytic subvarieties of P^n are algebraic

### Grothendieck's Tohoku Paper (1957)
"Sur quelques points d'algebre homologique" established:
- Abelian categories as the natural setting for homological algebra
- Derived functors via injective resolutions
- Spectral sequences and their convergence
- The general framework for sheaf cohomology

### Deligne's Work (1970s)
- Theorie de Hodge I, II, III: Mixed Hodge structures
- La conjecture de Weil I, II: Proof of the Weil conjectures
- Poids (weights) in etale cohomology

### Beilinson's Work (1980s)
- Higher regulators and algebraic K-theory
- Motivic cohomology (joint with Lichtenbaum)
- Derived category of coherent sheaves on P^n (Beilinson's resolution)

### Voevodsky's Revolution (1990s-2000s)
- A^1-homotopy theory
- Triangulated categories of motives
- Proof of Milnor conjecture (Fields Medal 2002)
- Motivic cohomology operations
- Notes on the Motivic Eilenberg-MacLane Spectrum

### Modern Synthesis (2010s-present)
- Bhatt-Morrow-Scholze: Integral p-adic Hodge theory
- Bhatt-Scholze: Prisms and prismatic cohomology
- Clausen-Scholze: Condensed mathematics
- Lurie: Spectral algebraic geometry
- Gaitsgory-Rozenblyum: D-modules and ind-coherent sheaves
- Toen-Vezzosi: Derived algebraic geometry
-/

